<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="394" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[140,1108,377,756]" pageId="37" pageNumber="394">
This Holarctic species was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peck and Cook" box="[638,902,448,474]" firstAuthor="Peck" pageId="37" pageNumber="394" pagination="723 - 787" refId="ref23804" refString="Peck SB, Cook J (2002) Systematics, distributions, and bionomics of the small carrion beetles (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Cholevinae: Cholevini) of North America. The Canadian Entomologist 134: 723 - 787." type="journal article" year="2002">Peck and Cook (2002)</bibRefCitation>
from Newfoundland and 
<collectingRegion box="[250,433,483,510]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="37" pageNumber="394">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
(Fig. 12). The source of the 
<collectingRegion box="[770,952,483,510]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="37" pageNumber="394">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
record (from the Charlotte County area) could not be determined (S. Peck, pers. comm.), nor were vouchers specimens found in any collection consulted. Consequently it is removed from the 
<collectingRegion box="[244,423,589,615]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="37" pageNumber="394">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
faunal list. Its status in Newfoundland should also be further investigated since there are no records in the province apart from the specimens listed above. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spence" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[220,454,659,685]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Sciodrepoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="watsoni">
<emphasis box="[220,454,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="394">Sciodrepoides watsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has primarily been collected in forested habitats but it is also tolerant of open old fields and grasslands where it is found on carrion and in mammal nests (
<bibRefCitation author="Peck and Cook" box="[259,503,730,756]" firstAuthor="Peck" pageId="37" pageNumber="394" pagination="723 - 787" refId="ref23804" refString="Peck SB, Cook J (2002) Systematics, distributions, and bionomics of the small carrion beetles (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Cholevinae: Cholevini) of North America. The Canadian Entomologist 134: 723 - 787." type="journal article" year="2002">Peck and Cook 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
